The paper discusses a new generalized Dictionary-Restricted Isometry Property (D-RIP) sparsity bound constant for compressed sensing. This topic falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves mathematical optimization techniques, which could place it under the Mathematical Modeling (cs.MM) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
